Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 12:02:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yonder</span><hr size=1> Just a note, I'm only 29, but every time I've used Yonder it's taken me at least one full real minute of running to get back to where I started.  I've used it in iceclad, and ALWAYS end up in the water.  I used it in RM near the tower while hunting HGs with a lvl 50 pal and landed far enough away that when I climbed the nearest wall I couldn't see the tower that I had left.  I've used it in SK near the spires and gotten temporarily lost because i was so far away from landmarks).  So I ALWAYS have yonder up.  And the only times it's failed me has been if channeling failed me.  So I'm not sure what the problems with this is.<br>
Fade and Shadow Step work like crap.  but I LOVE yonder. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoramon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goramon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 7:19:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yonder</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, but me turning into a ball of tangible energy flying along at bolt speed is facking uber.  But, here's what would happen...<br>
<br>
Chanters would bitch/moan/complain cause we're turning into something else, that they should get the spell...<br>
<br>
Druids/Shamans/Bards would bitch/moan/complain because sow just isn't fast enough anymore.<br>
<br>
Here's what it would take to get the spell live.  Spell duration would be based on stamina - or - 20 seconds.  You would have falling damage if you flew off a ledge (read, use levitate).  It would have a 30 second cast time, with a 5 minute recast time.  And, it would cost 500mana.  There's no way in hell they'd give this to us.  It doesn't fit in &quot;The Vision (tm)&quot;.<br>
<br>
